body:
It firstly happened around a month ago.
While I am in a champion select and I try to switch my masteries or runes, it does not change it and after around 10 seconds I get a notification that I lost my connection with pvp.net. After it reconnects (around 15 seconds) I can switch them without an issue. Sometimes it drops me out of a champion select and causes a time penalty. Game itself works fine, I have no connection problems at all and normal ping. It does not matter what client I use (old or new one) - it still happens. I don't have ipv6 connection, but I heard disabling ipv6 helper and using Microsoft Easyfixes helped some people. It did not help me tho. I currently use Windows 7 Ultimate 64-bit and used Windows 10 64-bit when it firstly happened.

Things I've done so far:
-reinstalled Windows two times;
-disabled ipv6 helper;
-changing dns;
-used hextech repair tool;
-reinstalled league;
-autorepaired league;
-used easyfixes to prefer ipv4 over ipv6 and disable ipv6;
-disabled ipv6 in windows network interface.
